design_brief_for_codex.party_display_formatter:
Add `muno/travel/src/utils/formatParty.ts` (or wherever the project keeps UI helpers):

```ts
export function formatParty(party: {
  adults: number;
  children?: Array<{ age?: number | null }>;
  rooms?: number;
} | null | undefined): string {
  if (!party) return '';
  const parts: string[] = [];
  if (party.adults) parts.push(`${party.adults} ${party.adults === 1 ? 'adult' : 'adults'}`);
  if (party.children && party.children.length > 0) {
    const ages = party.children.map(c => c.age != null ? `${c.age} yr${c.age === 1 ? '' : 's'}` : null).filter(Boolean);
    parts.push(
      `${party.children.length} ${party.children.length === 1 ? 'child' : 'children'}` +
      (ages.length > 0 ? ` (${ages.join(', ')})` : '')
    );
  }
  if (party.rooms && party.rooms > 1) parts.push(`${party.rooms} rooms`);
  return parts.join(' · ');
}
```

This is a translatable helper — wire i18n later (could move to react-i18next plurals in a follow-up round). For v1 the strings are English-only.

**Apply at** at minimum:
- `muno/travel/src/components/widgets/ItinerarySummary.tsx` — where party currently renders.
- `muno/travel/src/components/widgets/PropertyBlock.tsx` — the right-pane Trip state slot accumulator.
- Anywhere else the agent's payload includes party that gets rendered.

Add a vitest test for `formatParty` covering: zero children, 1 adult / 1 child / 1 room, 2 adults / 0 children / 1 room, 2 adults / 2 children (3 and 7 yrs) / 1 room, missing rooms field, null input, missing age on a child.
